CRITICAL LIVEWIRE 4 RULES:
- wire:model is LAZY by default — always add .live when real-time sync is needed
- Use #[Computed] for all derived data — never compute in render()
- Use $this->dispatch() — never $this->emit()
- Use #[On('event-name')] — never protected $listeners = []
- Use #[Validate] inline — never protected $rules = []
- Use wire:navigate for internal links — enables SPA mode
- Use wire:confirm for destructive actions — no custom JS confirm dialogs
- Use #[Locked] on any property that must not be modified from the frontend
- Use @teleport('body') for modals and overlays
- Use wire:loading.class / wire:loading.attr for loading states on buttons
- Use Volt for simple, self-contained UI pieces; use full Component class for complex logic
- All components must type-hint all public properties (int, string, bool, array)
- Use validateOnly() for per-step multi-form validation